bug 1468909 - enforce that all given RP IDs be valid domain strings in webauthn r=qdot\n\nThe webauthn spec mandates that relying party identifiers (RP IDs) are valid\ndomain strings. This enforces that by ensuring that any passed-in RP IDs parse\ncorrectly when set as the host portion of a URL.\n\nhttps://w3c.github.io/webauthn/#relying-party-identifier", "files": ["dom/webauthn/WebAuthnManager.cpp", "dom/webauthn/tests/test_webauthn_make_credential.html", "dom/webauthn/tests/test_webauthn_sameorigin.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8454143705c34a1de11f879fa11fc3f9d79907e4", "parents": ["a96803397f189e48ad65ac8907f4c641e48bf499"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Keromnes \u003cjanx@linux.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1468811 - Sort clang-tidy checks alphabetically in tools/clang-tidy/config.yaml. r=sylvestre", "files": ["tools/clang-tidy/config.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "32fbc8568c717482b905a2df3e92e173e2c984e2", "parents": ["8454143705c34a1de11f879fa11fc3f9d79907e4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Keromnes \u003cjanx@linux.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1468811 - Fail static-analysis autotest when a clang-tidy check doesn't exist. r=sylvestre", "files": ["python/mozbuild/mozbuild/mach_commands.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e276f2617d4e8494c06e78660f71af722b534ac4", "parents": ["32fbc8568c717482b905a2df3e92e173e2c984e2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Keromnes \u003cjanx@linux.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1468811 - Re-enable clang-tidy check performance-faster-string-find. r=sylvestre\n\nIt already had test files, but wasn't actually enabled. Also add a mock internal\nstd::string::find signature; two comments about disabled checks; and fix a typo.", "files": ["tools/clang-tidy/config.yaml", "tools/clang-tidy/test/performance-faster-string-find.cpp", "tools/clang-tidy/test/structures.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "50e3a