umper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nar -\u003e 8452f03a8564\nbe -\u003e f7c11e86e0c2\nbg -\u003e 09faa5dced4e\nes-CL -\u003e eb41a0774677\neu -\u003e debed011db67\nff -\u003e 0568dbc9f471\nit -\u003e fabe33b9a18d\nka -\u003e 0d6fbb575dd5\nkm -\u003e a0688b24e365\nms -\u003e d76b27b54972\nmy -\u003e 78a1da61b25f\nnn-NO -\u003e 4d61476be829\npl -\u003e b0efdf387bbb\npt-BR -\u003e 50ee6948ed89\nsl -\u003e 38a6a5248082\nsr -\u003e 06ad6734338a\nte -\u003e 4b287f9baf81\ntr -\u003e 3acacaa26306\nzh-CN -\u003e 3337c2e62b35\nzh-TW -\u003e 400bbd687539", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3f625b66a12352ac79d4b43bd057c8abacc436f0", "parents": ["c6acba0610e171203a6d08c18da44a95d860f14e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1530872501, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9441": {"changesets": [{"author": "Razvan Caliman \u003crcaliman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1471914 - Check that the font editor pref is on before rendering it. r=pbro a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: C0uQkZCJ2Ck", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontsApp.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/fonts.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eb0b435eba5b60040f7273d55acd29d7ee1fc3f5", "parents": ["3f625b66a12352ac79d4b43bd057c8abacc436f0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1469914 - Prevent the HAL from registering duplicate observers; r=froydnj a=lizzard\n\nThis also replaces the custom logic in ObserverList with an nsTObserverArray\nwhich has all the necessary logic for stable iteration over a potentially\nchanging list of items. Unused dependencies were also removed.", "files": ["hal/Hal.cpp", "hal/Hal.h", "xpcom/ds/Observer.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3da147dac512da9368fbe9179c5ad72dc8c759e4", "parents": ["eb0b435eba5b60040f7273d55acd29d7ee1fc3f5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1469309 - Remove an unused sensor type; r=agaynor a=lizzard", "files": ["hal/Hal.cpp", "hal/HalSensor.h", "hal/sandbox/SandboxHal.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0915e733540199880a1529f7c0cb0b9a4fef09ae", "parents": ["3da147dac512da9368fbe9179c5ad72dc8c759e4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Willcox \u003csnorp@snorp.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1464610 - Don't use EGL_KHR_surfaceless_context on Mali devices r=jgilbert a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2YlTVo86u0c", "files": ["gfx/gl/GLContextProviderEGL.cpp", "gfx/gl/GLLibraryEGL.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3a7a791ef4ff5f7c04c7eb2713e4a9104810e8d0", "parents": ["0915e733540199880a1529f7c0cb0b9a4fef09ae"], "tags": []}], "date": 1530889768, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "9442": {"changesets": [{"author": "\"Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e\"", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 5a6eba66a37822ac6ea8b0ae1dd2f8526d024b37 with FIREFOX_62_0b6_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f76813bfbe458280c6aceb10dd126f8ea0c8c314", "parents": ["3a7a791ef4ff5f7c04c7eb2713e4a9104810e8d0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "\"Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e\"", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7c5489ba3276be19bd689bcc463b55a3a56ca789", "parents": ["f76813bfbe458280c6aceb10dd126f8ea0c8c314"], "tags": []}], "date": 1530890337, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9443": {"changesets": [{"author": "\"Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e\"", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 5a6eba66a37822ac6ea8b0ae1dd2f8526d024b37 with DEVEDITION_62_0b6_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "af29e6fccf0c023cd1b56fcd9f558b78ee48dd4f", "parents": ["7c5489ba3276be19bd689bcc463b55a3a56ca789"], "tags": []}], "date": 1530890518, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9444": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1468917 - part 1: Make TSFTextStore not create native caret if ATOK 2016 is active r=m_kato a=lizzard\n\nOld ATOK referred native caret position to decide its candidate window position.\nHowever, at least ATOK 2016 does not need to refer it.  Additionally, if we\ncreate native caret for ATOK 2016, the candidate window position, ATOK 2016\nrefers the native caret only when we cannot return expected rect.  Therefore,\nonly immediately after modifying composition string, the position is different\nfrom actual position by a couple of pixels and that looks like flicks the\ncandidate window.\n\nSo, we should stop creating native caret for ATOK 2016 (as same as ATOK 2017).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LsmVXCmRIzc", "files": ["widget/windows/TSFTextStore.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b5967b6eb0a9b61be56f9cf6138ee251868b21cb", "parents": ["af29e6fccf0c023cd1b56fcd9f558b78ee48dd4f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1468917 - part 2: TSFTextStore::GetTextExt() shouldn't return TS_E_NOLAYOUT when ATOK retrieves text rects *in* the composition string r=m_kato a=lizzard\n\nCurrently, TSFTextStore::GetTextExt() won't return TS_E_NOLAYOUT error when\nATOK retrieves text rect of all of the composition string.\n\nHowever, if user converts 2nd or later clause, ATOK retrieves text rect after\nstart of the character of selected clause.  Returning TS_E_NOLAYOUT in this\ncase causes candidate window being positioned temporarily below first character\nof the composition string.\n\nFor avoiding the flicker of the candidate window, TSFTextStore::GetTextExt()\nshouldn't return TS_E_NOLAYOUT when ATOK retrieves text rects *in* the\ncomposition string.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Cp17HmP2QGK", "files": ["widget/windows/TSFTextStore.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "462984c1b4ffb94d76c7362d84867c2b3590eb19", "parents": ["b5967b6eb0a9b61be56f9cf6138ee251868b21cb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Erica Wright \u003cewright@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1471523 - Update Events.yaml for about:welcome events. r=ursula a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1Znb0QIWCSn", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Events.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "43f3051e9efa7b39531644a7b2f82f62f7b0eb4e", "parents": ["462984c1b4ffb94d76c7362d84867c2b3590eb19"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Seward \u003cjseward@acm.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1467415 - Importable mutable globals break alias analysis.  r=lth a=lizzard\n\nCurrently, do-these-references-alias queries for Wasm global variable\naccesses are handled incorrecty.  We fail to identify the case where both\nreferences are indirect (that is, imported) as possibly-aliasing.  This can\nlead to incorrect code generation in some pretty simple cases involving\nglobals, when compiling Wasm via IonMonkey.\n\nThis commit fixes that.  It also adds clarifying comments to\nMWasmLoadGlobalVar::congruentTo and MWasmLoadGlobalVar::valueHash pertaining\nto equivalance-of-loaded-values assessments.", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/wasm/regress/bug1467415.js", "js/src/jit/MIR.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4f29d9433d69f95e01796fd687f7035c267cb62c", "parents": ["43f3051e9efa7b39531644a7b2f82f62f7b0eb4e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Varga \u003cjan.varga@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470811 - Update FF 62 to know about upcoming new quota client; r=asuth a=lizzard", "files": ["dom/quota/ActorsParent.cpp", "dom/quota/Client.h", "dom/quota/QuotaManager.h", "dom/quota/test/unit/removeLocalStorage1_profile.zip", "dom/quota/test/unit/removeLocalStorage2_profile.zip", "dom/quota/test/unit/test_removeLocalStorage.js", "dom/quota/test/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "89c03b4aab112da9d4a0ac3a8d0e4be32315f366", "parents": ["4f29d9433d69f95e01796fd687f7035c267cb62c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Ratcliffe \u003cmratcliffe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1466880 - Track toolbox session id in event telemetry probes r=yulia a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: SC6Vm4Qn7n", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/toolbox-host-manager.js", "devtools/client/framework/toolbox.js", "devtools/client/inspector/markup/markup.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/views/rule-editor.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/views/text-property-editor.js", "devtools/client/inspector/toolsidebar.js", "devtools/client/responsive.html/manager.js", "devtools/client/responsive.html/test/browser/browser_telemetry_activate_rdm.js", "devtools/client/shared/telemetry.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/components/JSTerm.js", "devtools/docs/frontend/telemetry.md", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Events.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "13622431fb712c21c582fe78b6f1154146b0d7a8", "parents": ["89c03b4aab112da9d4a0ac3a8d0e4be32315f366"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mantaroh Yoshinaga \u003cmantaroh@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1468364 - Part 1. Calculate the created time of animation every creating the AnimationPlayerActor. r=daisuke a=lizzard\n\nThis patch will drop animationCreatedTimeMap in order to calculate created time\nevery creating the AnimationPlayerActor, as result of it, we can adjust the\ncurrent time even if AnimationsActor has the different current times of\nanimation.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DZ7m5wZcJF7", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/animation.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c599d36fb1a357867f0b66886cddb9e5aecaf76e", "parents": ["13622431fb712c21c582fe78b6f1154146b0d7a8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mantaroh Yoshinaga \u003cmantaroh@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1468364 - Part 2. Add animation inspector test which checks the created time when changing the playback rate and current time. r=daisuke a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HvLl67GaOhi", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/animation/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/animation/test/browser_animation_logic_adjust-time-with-playback-rate.js", "devtools/client/inspector/animation/test/browser_animation_logic_adjust-time.js", "devtools/client/inspector/animation/test/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e00ac12fb0dad0c257ae278f1feb0c1386c0279d", "parents": ["c599d36fb1a357867f0b66886cddb9e5aecaf76e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470355 - BufferWriter should stop reading data when the wanted amount has been reached, r=michal a=lizzard", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsNetUtil.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "14485670c0795d5ee019aa4a23b69927d5e946eb", "parents": ["e00ac12fb0dad0c257ae278f1feb0c1386c0279d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michal Novotny \u003cmichal.novotny\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470355 - Firefox is unresponsive when visiting https://www.youtube.com/premium, r=valentin a=lizzard\n\nThis patch avoids returning NS_BASE_STREAM_WOULD_BLOCK from CacheFileInputStream::ReadSegments when it was called with aCount=0.", "files": ["netwerk/cache2/CacheFileInputStream.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "db0c2c7b36318f970b417373d611ad9971c9bf98", "parents": ["14485670c0795d5ee019aa4a23b69927d5e946eb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Willcox \u003csnorp@snorp.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1467919 - Don't initialize PushService unless dom.push.enabled is true r=lina a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JfQUHf1JCRb", "files": ["dom/push/PushComponents.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2d9b44bd2d74fbb8f64d86b666e05bb08fa04a6b", "parents": ["db0c2c7b36318f970b417373d611ad9971c9bf98"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Willcox \u003csnorp@snorp.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1467919 - Don't try to clear PushService data if Push disabled r=baku a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IkImtSkmUAI", "files": ["toolkit/components/cleardata/ClearDataService.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3c8ab5a011e3e53fe125693ce8922314ffcf7a8b", "parents": ["2d9b44bd2d74fbb8f64d86b666e05bb08fa04a6b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1530997266, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "9445": {"changesets": [{"author": "Erica Wright \u003cewright@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472216 - in content search is allowed on about:welcome. r=ursula a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 15AOU9Q1LU", "files": ["browser/base/content/tab-content.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "83d54bf1905f4c71190b5438eeedb9fef3c55c4b", "parents": ["3c8ab5a011e3e53fe125693ce8922314ffcf7a8b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Parks \u003cdparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1449388 - Send NPNVaudioDeviceStateChanged to plugins when any Windows audio device changes state. r=jimm a=lizzard\n\nThis message allows plugins to detect when any audio devices change state, even when running inside of our plugin sandbox.", "files": ["dom/plugins/base/npapi.h", "dom/plugins/ipc/PPluginModule.ipdl", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginInstanceChild.cpp", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginInstanceChild.h", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginMessageUtils.h", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginModuleChild.cpp", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginModuleChild.h", "dom/plugins/ipc/PluginUtilsWin.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5f79cf2a5110c661dd49bddf6dccdc9cccea9050", "parents": ["83d54bf1905f4c71190b5438eeedb9fef3c55c4b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daisuke Akatsuka \u003cdakatsuka@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472684: Hide info bar and guides from highlighter. r=gl a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AAchCYg0d61", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/animation/animation.js", "devtools/client/inspector/animation/components/AnimationTarget.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6ab86ccd136dbaa90824c81ce76469ba83b80c71", "parents": ["5f79cf2a5110c661dd49bddf6dccdc9cccea9050"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daisuke Akatsuka \u003cdakatsuka@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472859 - Part 1: Avoid crashing which is in case the all values of keyframes are same. r=gl a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Bz60drhwohf", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/animation/components/keyframes-graph/ColorPath.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "79290fd284cfc2226df07b793287d9c2037f2f10", "parents": ["6ab86ccd136dbaa90824c81ce76469ba83b80c71"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daisuke Akatsuka \u003cdakatsuka@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472859 - Part 2: Add test for same colors and currentcolor. r=gl a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KRnajXPdwSq", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/animation/test/doc_multi_keyframes.html", "devtools/client/inspector/animation/test/keyframes-graph_keyframe-marker_head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e5972354da953a684cda4885accf6539eb09eae6", "parents": ["79290fd284cfc2226df07b793287d9c2037f2f10"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Boris Zbarsky \u003cbzbarsky@mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472829.  Add use counters for document.open.  r=smaug a=lizzard\n\nThe idea is to count non-no-op document.open and to count how many times that's\ndone with the replace argument set to \"replace\".", "files": ["dom/base/UseCounters.conf", "dom/html/nsHTMLDocument.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5db3df3d5a433545830b6199ba28d28c93ef5d34", "parents": ["e5972354da953a684cda4885accf6539eb09eae6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472520 - Fix a crash when generating image decoder telemetry. r=tnikkel a=lizzard\n\nIt is possible for a decoder's iterator to be invalid in some error\nconditions, all related to the ICO decoder seeking behaviour. Since we\nassume that the iterator is always valid for the purposes of generating\nthe decoder's telemetry data, a malformed ICO image could cause a crash.\n\nThis patch removes the assumption that the iterator is valid, and\nensures we don't add the decoder's data to telemetry if it is invalid.", "files": ["image/Decoder.cpp", "image/RasterImage.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ad56b08003a84f5bc1783cf38b760c41d9b915da", "parents": ["5db3df3d5a433545830b6199ba28d28c93ef5d34"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1473142 - Set browser.startup.blankWindow to true on Windows (ie. backout bug 1465583), r=mconley a=lizzard", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ab4de937c2d276d352627bbcb43eace6f3610c21", "parents": ["ad56b08003a84f5bc1783cf38b760c41d9b915da"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470516 - remove or fix localized values in securityInfo, r=rpl a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3xURSfbPTmS", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/schemas/web_request.json", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/mochitest/test_ext_webrequest_hsts.html", "toolkit/modules/addons/SecurityInfo.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "97d009f65f60e473a957ac5930589d8b2127a109", "parents": ["ab4de937c2d276d352627bbcb43eace6f3610c21"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Willcox \u003csnorp@snorp.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1467921 - Disable Web Push in GeckoView r=jchen a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 77tCU6T94LG", "files": ["mobile/android/app/geckoview-prefs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dfca0c7dd6d7cf5d3166b661151405cf51a0d103", "parents": ["97d009f65f60e473a957ac5930589d8b2127a109"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470684 - Flip undo close tab icon for RTL in all tabs menu r=dao a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: J5U4nwxYDZ1", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/tabs.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bfdba69be345c05d7c92be211bffa0217ab0826d", "parents": ["dfca0c7dd6d7cf5d3166b661151405cf51a0d103"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1469534 - Do not run Marionette tests for Android on release branches. r=dustin,tomprince a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ELuPdHw0ymb", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/test/marionette.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0a939a1cd7f97ed6fab45e9c9d33d86fd5f01ea1", "parents": ["bfdba69be345c05d7c92be211bffa0217ab0826d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1530999782, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "9446": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=mtabara\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D1969", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "79a74d674f47fb09c1a285d7eebdb5235f5e910d", "parents": ["0a939a1cd7f97ed6fab45e9c9d33d86fd5f01ea1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1531059394, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9447": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D2024", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "89ffee2e777769ae329d533c6be2b720ecec6b42", "parents": ["79a74d674f47fb09c1a285d7eebdb5235f5e910d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1531135930, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9448": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ed Lee \u003cedilee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472297 - Hide the existing onboarding button for users in the new simplified onboarding experience cohort. r=k88hudson a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: A4RMUGGCke7", "files": ["browser/extensions/activity-stream/content-src/components/Base/Base.jsx", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/content-src/styles/_activity-stream.scss", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-linux.css", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-linux.css.map", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-mac.css", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-mac.css.map", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-windows.css", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/css/activity-stream-windows.css.map", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js.map", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/install.rdf.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eac62098b0f6b53c87b9edf283257dc962154257", "parents": ["89ffee2e777769ae329d533c6be2b720ecec6b42"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ed Lee \u003cedilee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470170 - Implement priority system for AS Router messages. r=Mardak a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DZf2ccWEphW", "files": ["browser/extensions/activity-stream/content-src/asrouter/asrouter-content.jsx", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/content-src/asrouter/schemas/provider-response.schema.json", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js.map", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/install.rdf.in", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/lib/ASRouter.jsm", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/lib/ASRouterTargeting.jsm", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/lib/OnboardingMessageProvider.jsm", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/test/unit/asrouter/ASRouter.test.js", "browser/extensions/activity-stream/test/unit/asrouter/asrouter-content.test.jsx"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5dc16f73a43f37fd89b7ade43aa0cb9fe2c77310", "parents": ["eac62098b0f6b53c87b9edf283257dc962154257"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jamie Nicol \u003cjnicol@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470758 - Ensure we don't merge items with the same frame. r=mattwoodrow a=lizzard", "files": ["layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp", "layout/painting/nsDisplayList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1bff764743ffd981b1e6ddbe15072eeeb1d54e86", "parents": ["5dc16f73a43f37fd89b7ade43aa0cb9fe2c77310"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472076 - Introduce nsATimerAdjustmentObserver in nsRefreshDriver. r=birtles a=lizzard\n\nmMostRecentRefresh is changed not only in Tick() but also in\nEnsureTimerStarted().  In the case where it happens in Tick() refresh observers\ncan know it through WillRefresh(), but there is no way in the case of\nEnsureTimerStarted().  This patch introduces a new abstract class to be notified\nwhen mMostRecentRefresh was changed in EnsureTimerStarted() so that animations\ncan use the *real* most recent refresh time until the next tick happens.\n\nThe reason why we have another observer array in parallel with existing array\n(mObservers) is that the refresh driver should stop the timer if there is no\nnormal observes but there are still any timer adjustment observes.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FaDcl5GrvI3", "files": ["layout/base/nsRefreshDriver.cpp", "layout/base/nsRefreshDriver.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ae6851be89984fe2a74d35862ad25c59d20193aa", "parents": ["1bff764743ffd981b1e6ddbe15072eeeb1d54e86"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472076 - Update animations when the refresh driver's time changed due to the active timer changes. r=birtles a=lizzard\n\nNormally the refresh driver's time changes in nsRefreshDriver::Tick, and then\nDocumentTimeline::WillRefresh is called for the change.  But nsRefreshDriver\nsometimes updates its own time when their timer changes to the active one.\nThis patch lets DocumentTimeline update animations in response to the refresh\ndriver's time updates.  And thus this patch prevents animation state and\nrelevant stuff inconsistencies such as an animation has been finished without\nproper processes, e.g. without invalidating frame for the animation.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 42p5BWITQN0", "files": ["dom/animation/DocumentTimeline.cpp", "dom/animation/DocumentTimeline.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "76f1a92b24ca9b2a06d27da38eaf837dd762cfba", "parents": ["ae6851be89984fe2a74d35862ad25c59d20193aa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eitan Isaacson \u003ceitan@monotonous.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472623 - Don't use tts.getAvailableLanguages on Androids older than M. r=snorp a=lizzard", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/SpeechSynthesisService.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "33216e31fc3a81ea67e7cdde095ea93a58d5ec6b", "parents": ["76f1a92b24ca9b2a06d27da38eaf837dd762cfba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daisuke Akatsuka \u003cdakatsuka@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1473201: Change fill-opacity for color path to show actual color. r=jdescottes a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HlDpuKkM5Se", "files": ["devtools/client/themes/animation.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ecb1c1bf6f4829779354abfc0ca6e9d8fb1ab637", "parents": ["33216e31fc3a81ea67e7cdde095ea93a58d5ec6b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1460595 - Document the event ping r=Dexter,janerik a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ES8jW1xOQUd", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/collection/events.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/data/event-ping.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/data/main-ping.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/internals/preferences.rst"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5a480e17c6f5c15699dedd76e3e87e942516e5f0", "parents": ["ecb1c1bf6f4829779354abfc0ca6e9d8fb1ab637"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1460595 - Change storage semantics Telemetry Events r=Dexter a=lizzard\n\nInstead of a hard cap, introduce a topic to notify when we reach the now-\npreference-controlled per-process event record limit. Also add the capability\nto leave some records behind in storage for the next call.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EY40tqKxxeW", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Telemetry.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryEvent.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryEvent.h", "toolkit/components/telemetry/nsITelemetry.idl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6d2d353e5bfe8e794e6ca1f8a0a49dc677eab407", "parents": ["5a480e17c6f5c15699dedd76e3e87e942516e5f0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1460595 - Add Event Ping preferences to TelemetryUtils r=Dexter,janerik a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9gmYoMjiW3Y", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryUtils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b3b9d073cf2763e9b2e4272bce8c9a23212cd21", "parents": ["6d2d353e5bfe8e794e6ca1f8a0a49dc677eab407"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1460595 - Test \"event\" ping event storage r=Dexter,janerik a=lizzard\n\nI added checks that the new topic was appropriately notified and\nthat storage doesn't truncate upon hitting the limit, also covering the\ncase when there is a specified event limit for return.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FoSVvi7XSeM", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetryEvents.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7168e116a40670ddba4ee3b694a64ae923bddfe7", "parents": ["6b3b9d073cf2763e9b2e4272bce8c9a23212cd21"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1460595 - Implement the 'event' ping r=Dexter,janerik a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HQAk8jmouyI", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryController.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryEventPing.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0abaa980b795b7553aa9f1fdb8ad5f1eb0f06d14", "parents": ["7168e116a40670ddba4ee3b694a64ae923bddfe7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1460595 - Add meta-telemetry to record how many event pings we're sending r=Dexter,janerik a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7kxmvItSzEU", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryEventPing.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "602dd78381af870c37a513f972fc096234098051", "parents": ["0abaa980b795b7553aa9f1fdb8ad5f1eb0f06d14"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1460595 - Test the 'event' ping r=Dexter a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2SJCgXOQNEW", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetryEventPing.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "81e35fffdf70dbe5f3ad2ab58ce6d9350db909f6", "parents": ["602dd78381af870c37a513f972fc096234098051"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1460595 - Remove events from main pings and, thus, TelemetrySession r=Dexter a=lizzard l10n=strings-added-back-in-bug-1470493\n\nThis requires we take unsent event records out of about:telemetry since its\n\"Current Payload\" view only looks at the \"main\" ping.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GLs2EYvFaAF", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetrySession.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_ChildEvents.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetrySession.js", "toolkit/content/aboutTelemetry.js", "toolkit/content/aboutTelemetry.xhtml", "toolkit/locales/en-US/chrome/global/aboutTelemetry.dtd", "toolkit/locales/en-US/chrome/global/aboutTelemetry.properties"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "58935e7bb1480e7b2d08776fef1770edfe5eb340", "parents": ["81e35fffdf70dbe5f3ad2ab58ce6d9350db909f6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1463439 - Add a pref to enable 'event' ping. Defaults to true, except for GV. r=Dexter a=lizzard\n\nWhen it's false we also disable collecting events completely, in case the\nreason we're disabling it is due to storage issues.\n\nGeckoView doesn't presently support Events, so the 'event' ping is disabled by\ndefault for that platform.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9eKAtRiuER0", "files": ["mobile/android/app/geckoview-prefs.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryEvent.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryEventPing.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/TelemetryUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/internals/preferences.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetryEventPing_disabled.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3281d05908701c28a17589cadaec3550b430029b", "parents": ["58935e7bb1480e7b2d08776fef1770edfe5eb340"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1470493 - Render \"event\" ping events in about:telemetry r=janerik a=lizzard l10n=adding-strings-back-removed-in-bug-1460595\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8U54Cs6obOs\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D1882", "files": ["toolkit/content/aboutTelemetry.js", "toolkit/content/aboutTelemetry.xhtml", "toolkit/locales/en-US/chrome/global/aboutTelemetry.dtd", "toolkit/locales/en-US/chrome/global/aboutTelemetry.properties"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "32cde6cdb297933f18c086dfa4d6aed28a239a1a", "parents": ["3281d05908701c28a17589cadaec3550b430029b"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_62_0b7_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_62_0b7_RELEASE", "FENNEC_62_0b7_BUILD1", "FENNEC_62_0b7_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_62_0b7_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_62_0b7_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1531156961, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "9449": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrei Oprea \u003candrei.br92@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1472209 - Remove StartupOverlay if the about:welcome tour is skipped. r=ursula a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4L7nY14Ciae", "files": ["browser/extensions/activity-stream/content-sr