nrm -\u003e 5c1876d02125", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2c64ede0ba649a002337beb9370d31069ed886c4", "parents": ["eb4409cbddb406cb4275b175e534fa62c8375a8d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1534939225, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "9706": {"changesets": [{"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1476914 - Add fuzzy-if on Bug 1443902's reftests for Android. r=masayuki, a=test-only\n\nAndroid's reftest of Bug 1443902 is failed rarely (Bug 1476914, Bug 1475049\nBug 1477502 and Bug 1476129) due to \"image comparison, max difference: 1,\nnumber of differing pixels: 1\". But I don't know why difference is 1 and\nI think that this might be reftest framework for Android or Android emulator\nissue.\n\nSo I would like to add fuzzy-if as workaround.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3859", "files": ["editor/reftests/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ff3e20090e9a6f2006879f27092d939349d2668d", "parents": ["2c64ede0ba649a002337beb9370d31069ed886c4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=mtabara\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3944", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bcd42552273d760ff3f53f4d05f603779d1e8fbf", "parents": ["ff3e20090e9a6f2006879f27092d939349d2668d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1478848 - [fxui] Fix test_ssl_disabled_error_page to correctly wait for page load. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nCurrently the test doesn't wait for the restore button to become stale,\nand as such the call to find_element will return immediately with a\nreference to a \"h1\" element on the error page.", "files": ["testing/firefox-ui/tests/functional/security/test_ssl_disabled_error_page.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e6990f9e4bed67db217a013c54a10e5e192735d0", "parents": ["bcd42552273d760ff3f53f4d05f603779d1e8fbf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1480521 - Backport fixes from Bug 1479900. r=sfink, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3bP92eIdNIw", "files": ["js/src/jsfriendapi.h", "js/src/vm/Shape.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd432f7b82d6e2d29e80d20f2a1a48f89d863d19", "parents": ["e6990f9e4bed67db217a013c54a10e5e192735d0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447449 - [marionette] Prevent hang in pause action. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nUnder some unknown circumstances an instance of nsITimer doesn't\ncall resolve(), and as such the pause action hangs forever.\n\nInjecting a custom handler which itself calls resolve, prevents\nthis hang.\n\nThis is a workaround for older branches while bug 1484161 fixed\nit for Firefox 63.", "files": ["testing/marionette/action.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "55fc535ff4ceb31c76bc66c3ef777567754a4637", "parents": ["dd432f7b82d6e2d29e80d20f2a1a48f89d863d19"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447449 - [wdspec] Re-enable mouse_pause_dblclick.py. r=ato, a=test-only", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/webdriver/tests/actions/mouse_pause_dblclick.py.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9398d60a523c376e63d4c1e2a0ebb9109feedbc2", "parents": ["55fc535ff4ceb31c76bc66c3ef777567754a4637"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Comella \u003cmichael.l.comella@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1373964 - On profile migrate, delete \u003cdir\u003e/res/fonts. r=vladbaicu, a=RyanVM\n\nThe previous implementation attempted to delete files from /res/fonts (i.e.\nroot). I don't believe this was intended either:\nhttps://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=878674#c0 indicates the fonts\ndirectory should be inside the data dir of the application. The crash occurs\nwhen the /res/fonts directory exists (only some devices) but the user doesn't\nhave read access. If the user has write access, our code may actually delete\nthese system files: uh oh!\n\nMy fix is to change the deletion from /res/fonts to \u003cdir\u003e/res/fonts. I verified\nthis fix worked by creating a clean profile, adding dummy files to the\nres/fonts dir, and making sure only the correct ones were deleted (in zsh):\n\nexport DIR=/data/data/org.mozilla.fennec_mcomella; \\\n    adb shell pm clear org.mozilla.fennec_mcomella && \\\n    adb shell mkdir -p $DIR/res/fonts && \\\n    for i in touch.ttf lol.rdf; do adb shell touch $DIR/res/fonts/$i; done && \\\n    adb shell ls $DIR/res/fonts\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8atpcjYjGu0", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoApp.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "76136f7b8f3a5195ec1bd4d8a3f98c0a03d106bc", "parents": ["9398d60a523c376e63d4c1e2a0ebb9109feedbc2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alphan Chen \u003calchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1469348 - Fix the problem of download file failed on Mac. r=paolo, a=RyanVM\n\nIn this bug, we will focus on the problem of cannot download PDF file from google drawing successfully on MAC.\n\nAfter investigating, I found that \"SetTarget()\" is called twice with two different addresses.\nHowever, they both point to the same file.\nWe will assign the first target to \"mInitialTarget\" and the second one to \"mRenamedTarget\".\n\nThis problem happened when doing the second \"SetTarget()\".\nAfter canceling the existing AsyncCopy, we will schedule a new AsyncCopy.\nHowever, we only assign the mActualTarget with mRenamedTarget when they point to different files.\nIn this case, the two different addresses point to the same file.\nSo the mActualTarget is still the same as mInitialTarget.\n\nAfter completion of the AsyncCopy, we try to do \"CheckCompletion\".\nBut it will always return false due to \"mRenamedTarget exists\" and \"mActualTarget\" is not the same as \"mRenamedTarget\".\n\nThe solution is quite easy.\nWe should always update mActualTarget with renameTarget, even if they point to the same file.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3400", "files": ["netwerk/base/BackgroundFileSaver.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "809eb582affd16253b232eefe23631d4b33629bd", "parents": ["76136f7b8f3a5195ec1bd4d8a3f98c0a03d106bc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1534946655, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9707": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1481397 - Properly recalculate highest start timestamp when samples are removed. r=bryce, a=RyanVM\n\nSummary: When removing frames from the trackbuffer we may remove frames outside the original removal interval as we must remove all frames depending on the removed frames.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D2837", "files": ["dom/media/mediasource/TrackBuffersManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "809e1c8c76ab93bdd3d347133922c2070311fd37", "parents": ["809eb582affd16253b232eefe23631d4b33629bd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Guan-tin Chien \u003ctimdream@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1483408 - Set focus to the video element when the media document loads. r=Gijs, a=RyanVM\n\nFor some reason we might miss the initial focus event. This ensures the video\nelement is focused when the document loads.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D3444", "files": ["toolkit/content/TopLevelVideoDocument.js", "toolkit/content/tests/widgets/test_videocontrols_standalone.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bc6e295b9a0b2ec46e5dd05a0c3467a36bf3964f", "parents": ["809e1c8c76ab93bdd3d347133922c2070311fd37"], "tags": []}, {"author": "vinoth \u003ccegvinoth@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1480934 - Saving Reader View page yields blank page fixed by removing inline style. r=jaws, r=ckerschb, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D2947", "files": ["mobile/android/themes/core/aboutReader.css", "toolkit/components/reader/AboutReader.jsm", "toolkit/themes/shared/aboutReader.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a5ae6a7911df036fcb8561e490f5f0a8fc2b256", "parents": ["bc6e295b9a0b2ec46e5dd05a0c3467a36bf3964f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447449 - Fix ESLint max-len error. r=ato, a=bustage", "files": ["testing/marionette/action.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ede263f631010c7817dc224f456d6021e4ab35c", "parents": ["4a5ae6a7911df036fcb8561e490f5f0a8fc2b256"], "tags": []}], "date": 1534952233, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "9708": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nar -\u003e d19f928be85e\nca -\u003e acdaa9df55f2\neo -\u003e f7861bb7a0fd\nfa -\u003e 60ce85bde751\nhi-IN -\u003e 926c1e503a8b\nid -\u003e 6de33a21d92c\nmy -\u003e ebdc1e466c5b\nte -\u003e 3261dc3c6ee3\nuk -\u003e 0f9b9ce5f4b4", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7668d588855a9b195519749dfedfe582fb9c6a09", "parents": ["0ede263f631010c7817dc224f456d6021e4ab35c"], "tag